    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="766"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d766">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.24/279: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Burdett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-06T19:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 6, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 6—6:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>639. Reference Embassy’s telegram No. 636, December 6, 3 p.m. The Rio press today
                    published interviews with the Argentine and Chilean Ambassadors and the
                    Dominican Minister here each warmly supporting the Brazilian case in the recent
                    maritime incidents.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Burdett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
